race.comment: KING'S SECRET (13) exciting sprinter starting to build a good winning CV. Stalked the good speed second-up when a dominant winner as fav over 1100m at Randwick in BM94 class. Gets his chance on the limit, although he meets a few of these worse at the weights. THE INSTRUCTOR (1) resumes after finishing a respectable sixth in the G1 Stradbroke Hcp at Eagle Farm last June. Fitted with the two slick trials and puts himself in the right position from the gate. Leading player. SPYWIRE (9) strengthened over the break and the two runs back have been excellent. Sat on the good tempo when a gritty third over this trip in the Wyong Magic Millions 3&4yo Classic. Has further improvement to come and not without top-three claims from the good gate. BARBER (5) frustrating gelding who can race a little closer today from the low draw. Will relish the fast tempo and gets his chance.
